The President of the University of Texas approved a new plan that will allow for licensed concealed handgun holders to bring guns into classrooms and on campus. The President, Gregory Fenves, has been forced to allow such rule under the so called state \"campus carry law.\" Fenves said, \"I do not believe handguns belong on a university campus, so this decision has been the greatest challenge of my presidency to date.\" Certain regulations are in place, such as exclusion zones for where guns will not be allowed.

