On Thursday, a University of Texas advisory committee composed of faculty and staff agreed to allow handguns in classrooms. The \"campus carry\" law will go into effect on August 1st, 2016, and allow 21 year olds who possess a concealed handgun license to carry firearms in classrooms and buildings throughout its Austin campus. The University of Texas is one of the nation\'s largest schools, with an enrollment of more than 214,000 students, It was also the site of one of the nations first mass killings, when engineering and former Marine Charles Whitman killed 16 people on August 1st of 1966. The law will go into effect on the 50th year anniversary of that incident.

