According to a CBS affiliate, the University of Texas will allow concealed handgun license holders to bring their guns into its classrooms. University of Texas at Austin President Gregory L. Fenves announced the new campus carry rules on Wednesday this week a post on the university\'s website. According to local media, Texas state law will require all public universities to allow licensed concealed handguns owners in the classroom by August 1. Under University of Texas\'s new policies, certain laboratories, areas where pre-K-12 programs are held, and university residences will be considered gun exclusion zones, but not classrooms. Employees with private offices will also be able to prohibit handguns inside them.

